  "optimization_notes": "Root cause: main_scan was dominated by unnecessary per-row anti-join lookup work before exploiting the highly selective date window; this is primarily a work-elimination issue (Category C) with plan restructuring. The revised plan performs zonemap pruning and predicate-only scanning first to materialize candidate rowids, then applies anti-join only to candidates with a cache-resident bloom prefilter before exact index lookup, and aggregates only surviving rows. This reduces random pre-index probes and late-loads join/group columns only when needed.",
